summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1217 of the City of Seattle entitled: "An ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of 5th Avenue, a street in the City of Ballard, over and across tracts numbered 49 and 50, of Farmdale Homestead, situated in section 1, township 25 north, range 3 east, W.M., and providing for the taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor; for the ascertainment and payment of the just compensation to be made for the private property benefited and for the purpose of making such compensation" approved February 27, 1907.
